WEBVTT

00:04.471 --> 00:05.439 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.472 --> 00:06.440 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.473 --> 00:08.175 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.208 --> 00:09.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
The issue, plain and simple,
came down to

00:09.910 --> 00:10.878 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a matter of trust.

00:10.911 --> 00:13.547 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Turnover at the
White House.

00:13.580 --> 00:18.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have the latest on the
resignation of President
Trump's national security
adviser.

00:18.886 --> 00:24.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: Ahead of Israeli Prime
Minister Netanyahu's
visit to the White House, a look
at possible

00:24.691 --> 00:28.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
changes in Middle East policy
under the Trump
administration.

00:28.695 --> 00:35.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Plus, a story of hope -- how one
Kansas school
is helping homeless students
overcome the

00:35.636 --> 00:38.038 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
challenges they face outside the
classroom.

00:38.071 --> 00:40.474 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALIK CUSHON, Student: I got to
think about
what I'm eating for the night.

00:40.507 --> 00:43.143 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I got to think about how bills
are going to
get paid.

00:43.176 --> 00:45.846 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I got to think about all this
extra stuff.

00:45.879 --> 00:49.416 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:49.449 --> 00:52.185 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:52.219 --> 01:02.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: He served just 24
days, the
shortest tenure ever for a
president's national

01:02.329 --> 01:07.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: He served just 24
days, the
shortest tenure ever for a
president's national

01:07.734 --> 01:09.469 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
security adviser.

01:09.503 --> 01:14.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now Michael Flynn has been
forced out, but
the firestorm over his
resignation has just

01:14.708 --> 01:15.709 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
begun.

01:15.742 --> 01:18.078 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
John Yang reports on this day of
turmoil.

01:18.111 --> 01:22.950 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: President Trump knew
since late
last month that his Michael
Flynn had misled

01:22.983 --> 01:26.253 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the White House about his
telephone conversation
with the Russian ambassador.

01:26.286 --> 01:28.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
We have been reviewing and
evaluating this

01:28.922 --> 01:33.894 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
issue, with respect to General
Flynn, on a
daily basis for a few weeks,
trying to ascertain

01:33.927 --> 01:35.696 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the truth.

01:35.729 --> 01:38.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Press Secretary Sean
Spicer said
the warning came from acting
Attorney General

01:38.832 --> 01:41.802 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sally Yates, based on an NSA
phone intercept.

01:41.835 --> 01:45.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEAN SPICER: The White House
counsel informed
the president immediately.

01:45.205 --> 01:49.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president asked them to
conduct a review
of whether there was a legal
situation there.

01:49.242 --> 01:51.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That was immediately determined
that there
wasn't.

01:51.211 --> 01:55.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That was what the president
believed at the
time, what he had been told, and
he was proved

01:55.082 --> 01:56.817 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to be correct.

01:56.850 --> 02:00.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The issue, pure and simple, came
down to a
matter of trust, and the
president concluded

02:00.954 --> 02:03.590 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he no longer had the trust
of his national
security adviser.

02:03.624 --> 02:07.894 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Flynn had denied
publicly, and
to vice president-elect Pence
directly, that

02:07.928 --> 02:12.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he had discussed U.S. sanctions
with the Russian
ambassador to the United States
during the

02:12.733 --> 02:13.667 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
transition.

02:13.700 --> 02:16.036 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It came out last week that he
had.

02:16.069 --> 02:21.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, Spicer argued Flynn
didn't break the
law against private citizens
conducting diplomacy.

02:21.675 --> 02:26.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER: There is nothing
that the general
did that was a violation of any
sort.

02:26.713 --> 02:32.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was well within his duties to
discuss issues
of common concern between the
two countries.

02:32.619 --> 02:35.922 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I will say it again: What this
came down to
is a matter of trust.

02:35.956 --> 02:41.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: By last night, Spicer
said, the
president asked for Flynn's
resignation.

02:41.361 --> 02:47.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, Mr. Trump ignored shouted
questions
about Flynn.

02:47.401 --> 02:53.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Instead, he tweeted: "The real
story here
is, why are there so many
illegal leaks coming

02:53.407 --> 02:55.108 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out of Washington?"

02:55.142 --> 02:58.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER: It's not just
something that
is plaguing the current
situation, but it

02:58.578 --> 03:02.482 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
goes back to the Obama
administration, the
Bush administration, the Clinton
administration.

03:02.516 --> 03:07.854 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
When we have government
employees that are
entrusted with this and then
leak it out,

03:07.888 --> 03:09.589 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that undermines our national
security, frankly.

03:09.623 --> 03:13.994 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: At the Capitol, House
Speaker Paul
Ryan agreed that Flynn had to
go.

03:14.027 --> 03:15.695 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:15.729 --> 03:16.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: I
think the president made the
right decision

03:16.396 --> 03:18.131 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to ask for his resignation.

03:18.165 --> 03:22.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You cannot have a national
security adviser
misleading the vice president
and others.

03:22.202 --> 03:26.306 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Ryan wouldn't say if
he thinks
an investigation is needed.

03:26.339 --> 03:32.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
House Oversight Committee
Chairman Jason Chaffetz
said: "The situation has taken
care of itself."

03:32.512 --> 03:37.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Senate Majority Leader Mitch
McConnell said
it's highly likely that the
Senate will investigate.

03:37.818 --> 03:39.553 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:39.586 --> 03:40.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: The
Intelligence Committee is
already looking

03:40.520 --> 03:44.958 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at Russian involvement in our
election.

03:44.991 --> 03:50.797 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they have broad jurisdiction
over the
intel community writ large.

03:50.831 --> 03:53.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they can look at whatever
they choose
to.

03:53.967 --> 03:57.304 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Top Democrats
demanded an independent
probe.

03:57.337 --> 03:58.538 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:58.572 --> 04:01.908 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ELIJAH CUMMINGS (D), Maryland:
Do you hear
the silence?

04:01.942 --> 04:10.117 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is the sound of House
Republicans conducting
no oversight of President Trump.

04:10.150 --> 04:11.818 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Zero.

04:11.852 --> 04:17.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is what it sounds like when
they abdicate
their duty under the
Constitution.

04:17.591 --> 04:19.426 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:19.459 --> 04:21.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: There
are potential violations of law
here by General

04:21.828 --> 04:23.797 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Flynn and potentially others.

04:23.830 --> 04:30.504 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What I am calling for is an
independent investigation
with executive authority to
pursue potential

04:30.537 --> 04:32.305 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
criminal actions.

04:32.339 --> 04:36.676 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: In Moscow, the
Kremlin called it
an internal matter for the
United States.

04:36.710 --> 04:42.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But hard-line lawmakers like
Alexei Pushkov
said Flynn was the victim of a
witch-hunt.

04:42.382 --> 04:47.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump named retired Army
Lieutenant General
Keith Kellogg as his acting
national security

04:47.554 --> 04:49.356 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
adviser.

04:49.389 --> 04:53.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's served as chief of staff
for the National
Security Council and advised Mr.
Trump during

04:53.527 --> 04:55.428 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
his campaign.

04:55.462 --> 04:59.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The leading contenders for a
permanent replacement
are widely reported to include
former Vice

04:59.900 --> 05:06.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Admiral Robert Harward, a
retired Navy SEAL,
and former CIA Director and
retired Army General

05:06.339 --> 05:08.108 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
David Petraeus.

05:08.141 --> 05:13.847 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Petraeus is currently on
probation for revealing
classified intelligence to his
mistress.

05:13.880 --> 05:18.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Spicer said the president did
not know that
Flynn had discussed U.S.
sanctions with the

05:18.185 --> 05:24.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ambassador until acting Attorney
General Yates
contacted the White House on
January 26.

05:24.391 --> 05:30.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Spicer stressed that Flynn's
firing had nothing
to do with the phone call itself
-- Judy.

05:30.297 --> 05:33.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, John, there
are so many
threads to this story.

05:33.333 --> 05:37.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Among other things, we're
learning that the
FBI interviewed General Flynn
very shortly

05:37.871 --> 05:40.373 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
after the new administration
took office.

05:40.407 --> 05:44.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What are the questions at the
White House
about -- how are they answering
these questions

05:44.444 --> 05:50.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about why it took so long, from
then until
now, for this to unfold, to come
out?

05:50.517 --> 05:55.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: What they say is that
this had
been reviewed for weeks and that
it only was

05:55.522 --> 05:59.192 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the last night that Mr. Trump
decided to
ask for his resignation.

05:59.226 --> 06:05.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was also last night that The
Washington
Post reported this contact from
the acting

06:05.165 --> 06:07.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
attorney general with the White
House.

06:07.100 --> 06:10.337 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The interview story you
mentioned is from
The New York Times.

06:10.370 --> 06:17.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They quote current and former
officials, unnamed,
saying that they found Mr. Flynn
to be less

06:17.777 --> 06:23.350 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than forthcoming in these FBI
interviews immediately
after the inauguration.

06:23.383 --> 06:29.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If officials conclude that he
deliberately
lied to the FBI, that could lead
to a felony

06:29.823 --> 06:31.591 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
charge.

06:31.625 --> 06:33.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And just quickly,
John, how
is the White House dealing with
this overall?

06:33.693 --> 06:35.996 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: They are -- they came
out today.

06:36.029 --> 06:37.297 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They made a clean breast of it.

06:37.330 --> 06:43.003 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They tried to be as forthcoming
as they could
in the briefing.

06:43.036 --> 06:49.109 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sean Spicer stressed over and
over again this
was a matter of trust, that
Flynn was doing

06:49.142 --> 06:54.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
his job as preparing to be
national security
adviser by talking to the
ambassador.

06:54.547 --> 06:59.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They said it should be no
surprise that he
was talking about issues of
concern to both

06:59.686 --> 07:03.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of them, but they are hoping
that they can
put this to rest.

07:03.089 --> 07:06.893 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: John Yang at the
White House,
we thank you.

07:06.926 --> 07:11.164 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And at the other end of
Pennsylvania Avenue,
our Lisa Desjardins joins us for
the latest

07:11.197 --> 07:12.565 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from Capitol Hill.

07:12.599 --> 07:15.735 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, Lisa, we heard a little
about this already
in John's report.

07:15.769 --> 07:17.537 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But what are you picking up
there?

07:17.570 --> 07:21.941 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How are -- especially the
leadership in both
parties, how are they reacting?

07:21.975 --> 07:25.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The White House
may want
to put this to rest, but there's
no signs

07:25.245 --> 07:27.347 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of that happening at the Capitol
yet, Judy.

07:27.380 --> 07:30.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are two camps, especially
among Senate
Republicans.

07:30.350 --> 07:32.118 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's the place to watch.

07:32.152 --> 07:36.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some, like Senate Leader Mitch
McConnell,
say this should all be folded
into an ongoing

07:36.189 --> 07:40.026 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
investigation already under way
by the Senate
Intelligence Committee.

07:40.060 --> 07:43.730 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's over Russian hacking and
Russian manipulation
of the elections.

07:43.763 --> 07:47.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We know that will include now
questions about
General Flynn.

07:47.901 --> 07:49.669 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But that's only in private,
Judy.

07:49.703 --> 07:52.972 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Other Senate Republicans say
this needs to
have more light of day.

07:53.006 --> 07:56.643 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They want public hearings,
including a public
hearing with General Flynn.

07:56.676 --> 07:59.312 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's a divide for Senate
Republicans right
now.

07:59.346 --> 08:03.283 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Meanwhile, some other
Republicans say the
real investigation up here
should be into

08:03.316 --> 08:05.952 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the leaks, not into Mr. Flynn.

08:05.985 --> 08:07.721 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
These are all issues swirling
right now.

08:07.754 --> 08:09.756 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Lisa, what
about the Democrats?

08:09.789 --> 08:10.990 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Right.

08:11.024 --> 08:13.259 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Democrats came out strong
today, as John
reported.

08:13.293 --> 08:18.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Chuck Schumer, asking for this
independent
investigation, his folks told me
that could

08:18.231 --> 08:24.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
include the FBI investigation
under way, but
only if new Attorney General
Jeff Sessions

08:24.237 --> 08:25.705 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
recuses himself.

08:25.739 --> 08:28.041 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That is a critical point for
Democrats.

08:28.074 --> 08:32.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also, at the same time, they're
asking questions
about House Intelligence
Chairman Devin Nunes.

08:32.746 --> 08:38.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has generally been supportive
of General
Flynn, said he made a decision
to resign.

08:38.718 --> 08:40.387 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But he's not investigating.

08:40.420 --> 08:44.057 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Some point out that Mr. Nunes
was himself
on the Trump transition team.

08:44.090 --> 08:46.893 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I asked him about that, asked
his office about
that.

08:46.926 --> 08:49.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They said he will follow all the
leads that
he can.

08:49.729 --> 08:55.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, Democrats also eager
to point out
that another national security
issue arose

08:55.368 --> 09:00.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with Republicans in the past
couple of years
when they investigated Hillary
Clinton, a

09:00.073 --> 09:02.876 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Democrat, and they see this as
somewhat hypocritical.

09:02.909 --> 09:06.546 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa Desjardins,
so much to
follow.

09:06.579 --> 09:09.349 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you very much.

09:09.382 --> 09:13.486 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
In the day's other news:
Tensions with Russia
are rising on another front.

09:13.520 --> 09:19.025 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The New York Times reports that
Moscow has
deployed a new ground-launched
cruise missile,

09:19.058 --> 09:23.730 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ignoring U.S. complaints that it
violates
a 1987 treaty.

09:23.763 --> 09:31.404 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Obama administration
objected to the missile
during its testing phase in 2014
and 2015.

09:31.438 --> 09:36.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Five hundred U.S. troops arrived
in Romania
today as part of a mission to
shore up NATO

09:36.676 --> 09:38.845 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
allies in Eastern Europe.

09:38.878 --> 09:44.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Shipments of American tanks were
taken by
train to an air base after being
unloaded

09:44.284 --> 09:46.119 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at a Black Sea port.

09:46.152 --> 09:49.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The troops will be stationed
