25:37.903 --> 25:38.871 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
conversations.

25:38.904 --> 25:40.672 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

25:40.706 --> 25:44.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES RISCH: Well, I think
that's a different
inquiry, as to whether
conversations were

25:44.510 --> 25:48.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
condoned, depending upon what
the content
of the conversation was.

25:48.447 --> 25:53.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm very reluctant to talk about
a collision
between the two branches of
government on

25:53.685 --> 25:55.487 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
something like this.

25:55.521 --> 25:58.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator, you
started out by
pointing out the committee is
already looking

25:58.123 --> 26:02.227 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
into the Russian government's
