probably don't
do much harm.

27:16.201 --> 27:19.104 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When they are involved with
national security,
it is a big problem.

27:19.137 --> 27:23.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For the many years I have been
on the Intelligence
Committee, I have been concerned
about leaks.

27:23.075 --> 27:24.843 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So have other people.

27:24.877 --> 27:29.681 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I can tell you that, with the
great body of
intelligence information that is
out there,

27:29.715 --> 27:34.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not much of it has leaked out,
but even a
little bit of it being leaked
out is way too

27:34.286 --> 27:35.254 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
much.

27:35.287 --> 27:36.255 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is very dangerous.

27:36.288 --> 27:37.990 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It is un-American to leak.

27:38.023 --> 27:43.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It puts people's lives in
jeopardy, and it
really endangers the United
States.

27:43.095 --> 27:47.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Anyone who would leak national
security issues
should be ashamed of themselves,
and they

27:47.733 --> 27:49.134 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
are not a credit to America.

27:49.167 --> 27:52.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, as you
pointed out, very
little of it is leaked.

27:52.471 --> 27:54.206 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

27:54.239 --> 27:56.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES RISCH: Very little of it
is leaked,
but any can be important and can
put people's

27:56.675 --> 27:58.477 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
lives at risk.

27:58.510 --> 28:02.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator James
Risch with the
Senate Intelligence Committee,
thank you very

28:02.080 --> 28:03.048 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
much, Senator.

28:03.081 --> 28:04.049 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

28:04.082 --> 28:05.050 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JAMES RISCH: Thank you, Judy.

28:05.083 --> 28:06.919 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Good to be with you.

28:06.952 --> 28:09.254 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now for a
Democrat's perspective,
and for that, the vice chairman
of the Senate

28:09.288 --> 28:11.657 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Intelligence Committee, Mark
Warner of Virginia.

28:11.690 --> 28:16.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I began by asking what he
thought the Senate
should be doing about General
Flynn's discussions

28:16.361 --> 28:17.329 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with the Russian ambassador.

28:17.362 --> 28:18.797 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

28:18.830 --> 28:22.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK WARNER (D), Virginia: Well,
these discussions
are very troubling.

28:22.334 --> 28:26.605 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the first thing we need to
do is get to
the facts.

28:26.638 --> 28:31.710 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have heard reports that he
may have been
making certain statements that
were inappropriate

28:31.743 --> 28:33.812 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
